results.name: First occurrence of just n semiprimes occurs between the a(n)-th prime and the next prime.
comment: The first occurrence of k in A103668. - _Robert G. Wilson v_, May 07 2005
mathematica: fQ[n_] := Plus @@ Last /@ FactorInteger[n] == 2; f[n_] := Count[fQ /@ Range[Prime[n] + 1, Prime[n + 1] - 1], True];
